headline.print_headline: U.S. Denies Protections for Wolverines, Outrages Conservationists
headline.main: U.S. Denies Protections for Wolverines, Outrages Conservationists

lead_paragraph: U.S. wildlife managers on Tuesday denied federal protections for rare wolverines, outraging conservationists but pleasing Western states that opposed adding the reclusive but feisty member of the weasel family to the endangered and threatened species list.
